            "answer_text": "The title of the song \u201cRadio Ga Ga\u201d actually originates from Roger Taylor\u2019s infant son, Felix. Felix called the songs on the radio \u201cca-ca\u201d (slang for poo). Roger agreed with him as, at that time, the radio stations tended to play the Top Twenty hits all day long. Roger wrote the song, but altered the title to \u201cRadio Ga Ga\u201d. The video which accompanied it was yet another triumph by David Mallet and used the amazing film \u201cMetropolis\u201d for it. Thank You ",
